                            <comment id="466613" author="colmstea" created="Thu, 7 Aug 2025 14:32:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, AT uses parts of &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/verygreen/lustretester/blob/master/gerrit_build-and-test-new.py&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/verygreen/lustretester/blob/master/gerrit_build-and-test-new.py&lt;/a&gt; to analyze patches for additional testing. I have pushed a patch with the current version of the script.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;changed.py has a comment_only feature but it needs work. It was disabled due to ATM-3279. The logic to skip testing when changed.py returns comment_only=true is still active in AT so comment_only could be used for this ticket or a new key could be created to trigger a more relevant message to users.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
